  "body": "### Component\n\nAnvil\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [ ] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nIm trying to use anvil in order to write some tests in Rust. For this I need to deploy a contract. However deployment always fails with error `Out of gas: required gas exceeds allowance: 30000000`.\r\n\r\nThere is plenty of eth in the wallet, and I already tried to set `disable_block_gas_limit` with no effect. I also  increased `gas_limit` up to `u64::MAX`, but it gives the same error only with higher allowance mentioned. \r\n\r\nDo you have any idea what the problem might be and how to fix it? I appreciate any suggestions. You can find the code at [this link](https://github.com/webb-tools/relayer/blob/fa75a3ca9af64f1e2b481a822cb689fba06bf487/crates/tx-relay/tests/vanchor_private_transaction.rs).",
